-h ou --help:

~ no arguments lead to the main menu ~

-b <data-file>                                                                  ~ make a backup od the file ~

-r <data-file>                                                                  ~ restore the last backup ~

-f <data-file>                                                                  ~ enter in a data file, needed for most options ~

-f <data-file> -l                                                               ~ list elements, List within data file ~

-f <data-file> -d <budget>                                                      ~ delete a budget ~

-f <data-file> -n <budget>                                                      ~ new budget ~

-f <data-file> -B <budget>                                                      ~ enter directly in a budget ~

-f <data-file> -B <budget> -d <code>                                            ~ delete a paper of the given budget ~

-f <data-file> -B <budget> -l                                                   ~ list papers of the given budget ~

-f <data-file> -B <budget> -b <code> <value by unit> <quantity>       ~ add a new paper of the given budget, if exists modifies ~

-f <data-file> -B <budget> -s <paper> <value by unit> <quantity>                ~ sell the paper ~

-f <data-file> -B <budget> --simul <paper> <value by unit> <quantity>   ~ simulate a sell ~

